p: In retinol metabolism pathway, retinol, 9-cis-retinol and 11-cis-retinol metabolites were higher in mandarin fish of Group X than those of Group W, RDH (retinol dehydrogenase) gene expression was consistently higher in Group X (Fig.Â 3a). In glycerolipid metabolism pathway, triacylglycerol lipase gene expression was higher in mandarin fish of Group X, and glycerophosphoric metabolites was also higher in Group X (Fig. 3b). In biosynthesis of unsaturated fatty acids pathway, stearoyl-CoA gene expression and DPA (docosapentaenoic acid) metabolites were higher in fish of Group X than those in Group W (Fig. 3c).
